𝗛𝗘𝗔𝗗𝗦 𝗨𝗣 𝗶𝗧𝗔𝗠𝗔𝗥𝗔𝗪𝗦! 🔰

𝑩𝒆𝒇𝒐𝒓𝒆 𝒋𝒐𝒊𝒏𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑰𝑵𝑻𝑹𝑨𝑴𝑼𝑹𝑨𝑳𝑺 2025, 𝒍𝒆𝒕'𝒔 𝒓𝒆𝒂𝒅 𝒄𝒂𝒓𝒆𝒇𝒖𝒍𝒍𝒚 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑭𝒓𝒆𝒒𝒖𝒆𝒏𝒕𝒍𝒚 𝑨𝒔𝒌𝒆𝒅 𝑸𝒖𝒆𝒔𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏𝒔 (𝑭𝑨𝑸𝒔) 𝒕𝒐 𝒖𝒏𝒅𝒆𝒓𝒔𝒕𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝒎𝒆𝒄𝒉𝒂𝒏𝒊𝒄𝒔 𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝒘𝒉𝒂𝒕 𝒚𝒐𝒖 𝒘𝒊𝒍𝒍 𝒏𝒆𝒆𝒅 𝒕𝒐 𝒋𝒐𝒊𝒏. 

#RiseAboveCompetitions 
#INTRAMURALS2025
#RAC2526

𝗛𝗘𝗔𝗗𝗦 𝗨𝗣 𝗶𝗧𝗔𝗠𝗔𝗥𝗔𝗪𝗦! 🔰

𝑩𝒆𝒇𝒐𝒓𝒆 𝒋𝒐𝒊𝒏𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑰𝑵𝑻𝑹𝑨𝑴𝑼𝑹𝑨𝑳𝑺 2025, 𝒍𝒆𝒕'𝒔 𝒓𝒆𝒂𝒅 𝒄𝒂𝒓𝒆𝒇𝒖𝒍𝒍𝒚 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑭𝒓𝒆𝒒𝒖𝒆𝒏𝒕𝒍𝒚 𝑨𝒔𝒌𝒆𝒅 𝑸𝒖𝒆𝒔𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏𝒔 (𝑭𝑨𝑸𝒔) 𝒕𝒐 𝒖𝒏𝒅𝒆𝒓𝒔𝒕𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝒎𝒆𝒄𝒉𝒂𝒏𝒊𝒄𝒔 𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝒘𝒉𝒂𝒕 𝒚𝒐𝒖 𝒘𝒊𝒍𝒍 𝒏𝒆𝒆𝒅 𝒕𝒐 𝒋𝒐𝒊𝒏.

media.accessibility_caption: May be an image of text

May be an image of text that says "Who can join the Intramural 2025-2026? Any bonifide student of FEU Tech; and must be a registered member of the Recreation and Athletics Club (RAC). How much is the membership fee for joining RAC? The membership fee is 150 pesos per head. Technorun participants and FEUAL 2024 athletes are waived from the fee. How much is the registration fee for joining Intramural 2025-2026? The registration fee for team sports is 200 pesos per head, while indoor sports is 150 pesos per head. Technorun participants are waived from the fee."
May be a graphic of text

May be a graphic of text that says "What sports are included in the Intramural 2025-2026? Basketball Men's Volleyball Men's and Women's 3x3 Basketball (Women's) Table Tennis (Singles) Badminton (Singles) Chess Are students restricted to join in only one sport? Students can join multiple sports. Who can register in the Intramural 2025 Registration Form? Only team captains or team representatives can register. Make sure that upon registration, you are certain you are the team captain or representative, and that you will be forming a team."

May be a graphic of text that says "How will we submit our soft copy requirements? Once registered, team captains will receive a confirmation email with their designated Google Drive link to upload all requirements. Please check your email regularly as confirmation emails may take up days to be sent. Where to submit the hard copy requirements? Hard copy requirements can be submitted in room F713- SCC/RSO Office. Will the jerseys for team sports be provided, or will the students supply them on their own? Each team must provide and supply their own jerseys."

𝗛𝗘𝗔𝗗𝗦 𝗨𝗣 𝗶𝗧𝗔𝗠𝗔𝗥𝗔𝗪𝗦! 🔰

media.accessibility_caption: May be an image of text

May be an image of text that says "Who can join the Intramural 2025-2026? Any bonifide student of FEU Tech; and must be a registered member of the Recreation and Athletics Club (RAC). How much is the membership fee for joining RAC? The membership fee is 150 pesos per head. Technorun participants and FEUAL 2024 athletes are waived from the fee. How much is the registration fee for joining Intramural 2025-2026? The registration fee for team sports is 200 pesos per head, while indoor sports is 150 pesos per head. Technorun participants are waived from the fee."
May be a graphic of text

May be a graphic of text that says "What sports are included in the Intramural 2025-2026? Basketball Men's Volleyball Men's and Women's 3x3 Basketball (Women's) Table Tennis (Singles) Badminton (Singles) Chess Are students restricted to join in only one sport? Students can join multiple sports. Who can register in the Intramural 2025 Registration Form? Only team captains or team representatives can register. Make sure that upon registration, you are certain you are the team captain or representative, and that you will be forming a team."

May be a graphic of text that says "How will we submit our soft copy requirements? Once registered, team captains will receive a confirmation email with their designated Google Drive link to upload all requirements. Please check your email regularly as confirmation emails may take up days to be sent. Where to submit the hard copy requirements? Hard copy requirements can be submitted in room F713- SCC/RSO Office. Will the jerseys for team sports be provided, or will the students supply them on their own? Each team must provide and supply their own jerseys."

May be an image of text that says "Who can join the Intramural 2025-2026? Any bonifide student of FEU Tech; and must be a registered member of the Recreation and Athletics Club (RAC). How much is the membership fee for joining RAC? The membership fee is 150 pesos per head. Technorun participants and FEUAL 2024 athletes are waived from the fee. How much is the registration fee for joining Intramural 2025-2026? The registration fee for team sports is 200 pesos per head, while indoor sports is 150 pesos per head. Technorun participants are waived from the fee."
May be a graphic of text

May be a graphic of text that says "What sports are included in the Intramural 2025-2026? Basketball Men's Volleyball Men's and Women's 3x3 Basketball (Women's) Table Tennis (Singles) Badminton (Singles) Chess Are students restricted to join in only one sport? Students can join multiple sports. Who can register in the Intramural 2025 Registration Form? Only team captains or team representatives can register. Make sure that upon registration, you are certain you are the team captain or representative, and that you will be forming a team."

May be a graphic of text that says "How will we submit our soft copy requirements? Once registered, team captains will receive a confirmation email with their designated Google Drive link to upload all requirements. Please check your email regularly as confirmation emails may take up days to be sent. Where to submit the hard copy requirements? Hard copy requirements can be submitted in room F713- SCC/RSO Office. Will the jerseys for team sports be provided, or will the students supply them on their own? Each team must provide and supply their own jerseys."

CHARGE, TAMARAWS, CHARGE TO LUNETA! ✊️

We invite all Tamaraws who are sick of corrupt governance and that deceitful administration sitting in Malacañang to join forces with other student-youth and sectors of Filipino society in protests this September 19 and 21. 

Let this shake all those parasitic public officials that the Filipino people have always been ready to stand against corruption and nepotism in our society.

Tomorrow, September 19, we organize a Black Friday Protest: 
4:00 pm - Assembly @ P. Noval
5:00 pm - March to FEU Gate 4, then Program

On September 21, our program is as follows: 
8:00 am - Assembly of One Ubelt @ Kartilya ng Katipunan
9:00 am - March to Luneta 

Kindly Scan the QR Code in order to join the Messenger group chat of attendees ❤

Join KPL FEU!
https://forms.gle/3hDXd5jQP6HAEm3x7

#MarcosSingilinDutertePanagutin
#NotoCorruption

message.text:
CHARGE, TAMARAWS, CHARGE TO LUNETA! ✊️

We invite all Tamaraws who are sick of corrupt governance and that deceitful administration sitting in Malacañang to join forces with other student-youth and sectors of Filipino society in protests this September 19 and 21. 

Let this shake all those parasitic public officials that the Filipino people have always been ready to stand against corruption and nepotism in our society.

Tomorrow, September 19, we organize a Black Friday Protest: 
4:00 pm - Assembly @ P. Noval
5:00 pm - March to FEU Gate 4, then Program

On September 21, our program is as follows: 
8:00 am - Assembly of One Ubelt @ Kartilya ng Katipunan
9:00 am - March to Luneta 

Kindly Scan the QR Code in order to join the Messenger group chat of attendees ❤

Join KPL FEU!
https://forms.gle/3hDXd5jQP6HAEm3x7

#MarcosSingilinDutertePanagutin
#NotoCorruption
#Luneta

message.text:
Celebrate 𝑾𝒐𝒓𝒍𝒅 𝑻𝒐𝒖𝒓𝒊𝒔𝒎 𝑫𝒂𝒚 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓 with us!

Join us on 𝗦𝗲𝗽𝘁𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝟮𝟯, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱, 𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝟭:𝟬𝟬 𝗣𝗠 𝘁𝗼 𝟱:𝟬𝟬 𝗣𝗠 𝗮𝘁 𝗙𝗘𝗨 𝗠𝗮𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿𝗶𝘂𝗺 as we highlight 𝐖𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓 with the theme of "𝑇𝑟𝑎𝑛𝑠𝑓𝑜𝑟𝑚𝑖𝑛𝑔 𝑇𝑟𝑎𝑣𝑒𝑙 𝑖𝑛𝑡𝑜 𝑆𝑢𝑠𝑡𝑎𝑖𝑛𝑎𝑏𝑙𝑒 𝑎𝑛𝑑 𝑀𝑒𝑎𝑛𝑖𝑛𝑔𝑓𝑢𝑙 𝑇𝑜𝑢𝑟𝑖𝑠𝑚." 

Get ready to learn and take bold steps to transform travel into sustainability and meaningful tourism. We have guest speakers to share and advocate their views and expertise into making a sustainable journey and creating meaningful memories. 

Participants will receive e-certificate after the event.

𝙎𝙘𝙖𝙣 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙌𝙍 𝙘𝙤𝙙𝙚 or through this link (https://forms.office.com/r/PhxMagSrwp) to 𝙧𝙚𝙜𝙞𝙨𝙩𝙚𝙧. 𝙋𝙧𝙚-𝙧𝙚𝙜𝙞𝙨𝙩𝙧𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙤𝙣 𝙤𝙥𝙚𝙣s 𝙪𝙣𝙩𝙞𝙡 𝙎𝙖𝙩𝙪𝙧𝙙𝙖𝙮, 7:00 𝙋𝙈

Don’t miss this exciting event and be part of a global celebration that inspires change and shapes the future of tourism. As one, let’s take the next step towards a more sustainable and meaningful journey. See you there!

#SustainableTourism

Join us on 𝗦𝗲𝗽𝘁𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝟮𝟯, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱, 𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝟭:𝟬𝟬 𝗣𝗠 𝘁𝗼 𝟱:𝟬𝟬 𝗣𝗠 𝗮𝘁 𝗙𝗘𝗨 𝗠𝗮𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿𝗶𝘂𝗺 as we highlight 𝐖𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓 with the theme of "𝑇𝑟𝑎𝑛𝑠𝑓𝑜𝑟𝑚𝑖𝑛𝑔 𝑇𝑟𝑎𝑣𝑒𝑙 𝑖𝑛𝑡𝑜 𝑆𝑢𝑠𝑡𝑎𝑖𝑛𝑎𝑏𝑙𝑒 𝑎𝑛𝑑 𝑀𝑒𝑎𝑛𝑖𝑛𝑔𝑓𝑢𝑙 𝑇𝑜𝑢𝑟𝑖𝑠𝑚." 

Get ready to learn and take bold steps to transform travel into sustainability and meaningful tourism. We have guest speakers to share and advocate their views and expertise into making a sustainable journey and creating meaningful memories. 

Participants will receive e-certificate after the event.

𝙎𝙘𝙖𝙣 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙌𝙍 𝙘𝙤𝙙𝙚 or through this link (https://forms.office.com/r/PhxMagSrwp) to 𝙧𝙚𝙜𝙞𝙨𝙩𝙚𝙧. 𝙋𝙧𝙚-𝙧𝙚𝙜𝙞𝙨𝙩𝙧𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙤𝙣 𝙤𝙥𝙚𝙣s 𝙪𝙣𝙩𝙞𝙡 𝙎𝙖𝙩𝙪𝙧𝙙𝙖𝙮, 7:00 𝙋𝙈

Don’t miss this exciting event and be part of a global celebration that inspires change and shapes the future of tourism. As one, let’s take the next step towards a more sustainable and meaningful journey. See you there!

#WorldTourismDay2025
#SustainableTourism 
#FEU
#FEU97th
#FEUITHM
#EventuraProduction

message.text:
Celebrate 𝑾𝒐𝒓𝒍𝒅 𝑻𝒐𝒖𝒓𝒊𝒔𝒎 𝑫𝒂𝒚 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓 with us!

Join us on 𝗦𝗲𝗽𝘁𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝟮𝟯, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱, 𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝟭:𝟬𝟬 𝗣𝗠 𝘁𝗼 𝟱:𝟬𝟬 𝗣𝗠 𝗮𝘁 𝗙𝗘𝗨 𝗠𝗮𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿𝗶𝘂𝗺 as we highlight 𝐖𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓 with the theme of "𝑇𝑟𝑎𝑛𝑠𝑓𝑜𝑟𝑚𝑖𝑛𝑔 𝑇𝑟𝑎𝑣𝑒𝑙 𝑖𝑛𝑡𝑜 𝑆𝑢𝑠𝑡𝑎𝑖𝑛𝑎𝑏𝑙𝑒 𝑎𝑛𝑑 𝑀𝑒𝑎𝑛𝑖𝑛𝑔𝑓𝑢𝑙 𝑇𝑜𝑢𝑟𝑖𝑠𝑚." 

Get ready to learn and take bold steps to transform travel into sustainability and meaningful tourism. We have guest speakers to share and advocate their views and expertise into making a sustainable journey and creating meaningful memories. 

Participants will receive e-certificate after the event.

𝙎𝙘𝙖𝙣 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙌𝙍 𝙘𝙤𝙙𝙚 or through this link (https://forms.office.com/r/PhxMagSrwp) to 𝙧𝙚𝙜𝙞𝙨𝙩𝙚𝙧. 𝙋𝙧𝙚-𝙧𝙚𝙜𝙞𝙨𝙩𝙧𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙤𝙣 𝙤𝙥𝙚𝙣s 𝙪𝙣𝙩𝙞𝙡 𝙎𝙖𝙩𝙪𝙧𝙙𝙖𝙮, 7:00 𝙋𝙈

Don’t miss this exciting event and be part of a global celebration that inspires change and shapes the future of tourism. As one, let’s take the next step towards a more sustainable and meaningful journey. See you there!

message.text:
Celebrate 𝑾𝒐𝒓𝒍𝒅 𝑻𝒐𝒖𝒓𝒊𝒔𝒎 𝑫𝒂𝒚 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓 with us!

Join us on 𝗦𝗲𝗽𝘁𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿 𝟮𝟯, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱, 𝗳𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝟭:𝟬𝟬 𝗣𝗠 𝘁𝗼 𝟱:𝟬𝟬 𝗣𝗠 𝗮𝘁 𝗙𝗘𝗨 𝗠𝗮𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝘂𝗱𝗶𝘁𝗼𝗿𝗶𝘂𝗺 as we highlight 𝐖𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝 𝐓𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐬𝐦 𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓 with the theme of "𝑇𝑟𝑎𝑛𝑠𝑓𝑜𝑟𝑚𝑖𝑛𝑔 𝑇𝑟𝑎𝑣𝑒𝑙 𝑖𝑛𝑡𝑜 𝑆𝑢𝑠𝑡𝑎𝑖𝑛𝑎𝑏𝑙𝑒 𝑎𝑛𝑑 𝑀𝑒𝑎𝑛𝑖𝑛𝑔𝑓𝑢𝑙 𝑇𝑜𝑢𝑟𝑖𝑠𝑚." 

Get ready to learn and take bold steps to transform travel into sustainability and meaningful tourism. We have guest speakers to share and advocate their views and expertise into making a sustainable journey and creating meaningful memories. 

Participants will receive e-certificate after the event.

𝙎𝙘𝙖𝙣 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙌𝙍 𝙘𝙤𝙙𝙚 or through this link (https://forms.office.com/r/PhxMagSrwp) to 𝙧𝙚𝙜𝙞𝙨𝙩𝙚𝙧. 𝙋𝙧𝙚-𝙧𝙚𝙜𝙞𝙨𝙩𝙧𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙤𝙣 𝙤𝙥𝙚𝙣s 𝙪𝙣𝙩𝙞𝙡 𝙎𝙖𝙩𝙪𝙧𝙙𝙖𝙮, 7:00 𝙋𝙈

Don’t miss this exciting event and be part of a global celebration that inspires change and shapes the future of tourism. As one, let’s take the next step towards a more sustainable and meaningful journey. See you there!

#WorldTourismDay2025
#SustainableTourism 
#FEU
#FEU97th
#FEUITHM
#EventuraProduction
